-- =============================================================================
-- S14. FORMAL VERIFICATION (Agda / Quint / TLA+)
-- =============================================================================
--
-- Quint (state machine bounded model checking):
--   1. IntentNeverLost: all ChatMessage eventually reach terminal state
--   2. Offset monotonicity: telegram offset never decreases
--   3. NonBlockingSelect: select loop never blocks > 100ms (model via timed automata)
--   4. Rate limiter correctness: no more than N messages per window are processed
--
-- TLA+ (temporal logic):
--   1. Liveness: every received message eventually gets responded/failed
--   2. Safety: no two pollers process the same message (offset-based deduplication)
--   3. Fairness: heartbeat cron fires within bounded time of interval
--   4. Simulator fidelity: response structure isomorphic to real API

