-- The OpenClaw chat interaction system is primarily headless (daemon), but its state
-- is exposed through the Gleam Triple-Interface Mandate:
--   1. Lustre Web UI: Chat history page at /chat (port 4100)
--   2. Wisp REST API: /api/chat/messages, /api/chat/send (port 4100)
--   3. TUI Terminal: Chat tab in the 15-tab split-screen dashboard
--
-- Dashboard elements:
--   - Message throughput sparkline (msgs/min)
--   - Channel status badges (Telegram: green/red, GChat: green/red)
--   - LLM inference latency histogram
--   - Rate limiter status per chat_id
--   - Simulator queue depths (if simulator active)

-- =============================================================================
-- S19. TESTING SPECIFICATION (coverage gates, BDD levels)
-- =============================================================================
--
-- Testing uses the Simulator API for deterministic E2E coverage:
--
-- L1 Unit:   SimState::new(), inject_telegram(), inject_gchat()
-- L2 Snapshot: Simulator HTTP response format validation
-- L3 Style:  JSON response structure matches real API
-- L4 Integration: Full cycle: inject -> poll -> cortex -> response -> outbox
-- L5 Responsive: Multiple concurrent messages from different channels
-- L6 Accessibility: ACK flow completes within 2s SLA
-- L7 E2E:    Playwright-style smoke via simulator inject -> outbox check
--
-- Math Gates:
--   Shannon H >= 2.5 bits (message classification entropy)
--   CCM >= 0.90 (cyclomatic complexity metric for intent routing)
--   ITQS >= 0.85 (integrated test quality score)

-- =============================================================================
-- S20. MATHEMATICAL STRUCTURES (algorithms, formulas, metrics)
-- =============================================================================
--
-- 1. Response Latency Histogram
--    - Buckets: [0-500ms, 500ms-1s, 1s-2s, 2s-5s, 5s-30s, 30s+]
--    - Percentiles: P50, P90, P99 tracked per channel
--    - SLA: ack_latency P99 < 2s, full_response P99 < 30s
--
-- 2. Message Throughput (msgs/sec)
--    - Sliding window: 60 seconds
--    - Formula: count(messages in window) / window_duration_secs
--    - Rate limiter trigger: throughput > config.rate_limit_max_msgs_per_minute / 60
--
-- 3. Stress Classification (linear mapping)
--    - f(stress) -> Priority:
--      if stress in [0.0, 0.5): return P2 (routine)
--      if stress in [0.5, 0.8): return P1 (high)
--      if stress in [0.8, 1.0]: return P0 (critical)
--    - Source: cortex.rs:154 — dynamic_priority derivation
--
-- 4. EMA for LLM Inference Latency
--    - alpha = 0.3 (same as build history EMA)
--    - EMA_new = alpha * latency_current + (1 - alpha) * EMA_previous
--    - Used to predict expected inference time for operator feedback
--
-- 5. Offset Delta Rate
--    - delta_rate = (offset_current - offset_previous) / time_elapsed_secs
--    - High delta_rate indicates burst; may trigger adaptive polling interval

